Sentencas: The anodic performance of CeO2 doped with Mn and Fe was studied by using a Co-doped LaGaO3-based oxide (LSGMC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Ce0.6(Mn0.3Fe0.1)O2 as an Oxidation-Tolerant Ceramic Anode for SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Oxide Electrolyte

Sentencas: The open-circuit potential approximate to the theoretical value (1.1 V) was exhibited on the cell using Ce(Mn,Fe)O-2 oxide for the anode.
Titulo: Ce0.6(Mn0.3Fe0.1)O2 as an Oxidation-Tolerant Ceramic Anode for SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Oxide Electrolyte

Sentencas: A high maximum power density (0.622 W/cm(2) at 1273 K) was attained by co-doping Mn and Fe into CeO2.
Titulo: Ce0.6(Mn0.3Fe0.1)O2 as an Oxidation-Tolerant Ceramic Anode for SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Oxide Electrolyte

Sentencas: After a few cycles of oxidation treatment at 1073 K, there was an increase in the maximum power density.
Titulo: Ce0.6(Mn0.3Fe0.1)O2 as an Oxidation-Tolerant Ceramic Anode for SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Oxide Electrolyte

Sentencas: Therefore, Mn- and Fe-doped CeO2 is a potential oxidation-tolerant oxide anode for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) using an LSGMC-based electrolyte.
Titulo: Ce0.6(Mn0.3Fe0.1)O2 as an Oxidation-Tolerant Ceramic Anode for SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Oxide Electrolyte
